{{!--
  Maintainer notes (not emitted in G-code):
  - 4-axis Heidenhain TNC post template — A-axis rotary (rotation around X by default).
  - Uses DIN/ISO mode (G-code) for Heidenhain TNC controls (TNC 640, TNC 530, iTNC 530).
  - Comments use semicolons: ; comment text.
  - Heidenhain TNC supports both Klartext (conversational) and DIN/ISO. This post
    uses DIN/ISO since our toolpath lines output standard G0/G1/G2/G3 format.
  - TOOL CALL is the Klartext equivalent; in DIN/ISO mode we use T + M6.
  - No TCPM (M128) — 4-axis indexed/continuous work does not require tool center
    point management. TCPM is only needed for simultaneous 5-axis. If your setup
    needs TCPM, use a 5-axis post instead.
  - G93 inverse-time feed mode is supported via the inverseTimeFeed context flag.
  - When enabled, G93 is emitted before toolpath and G94 is restored after.
  - Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
  - Additional context for 4-axis: axisCount, aAxisRangeDeg, aAxisOrientation.
--}}
; {{machine.name}} — {{machine.id}}
; 4-AXIS (A-ROTARY) G-CODE — Heidenhain TNC (DIN/ISO mode)
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Heidenhain TNC manual
; before running on a machine. Output is not guaranteed safe for any machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Switch the TNC to DIN/ISO mode (not Klartext). This program uses
;     standard G-code, not Heidenhain conversational format.
; (2) Confirm the rotary table or chuck is firmly clamped and the A-axis
;     motor is enabled in machine parameters (MP).
; (3) Confirm the workpiece is centred on the rotary axis — off-centre
;     stock causes gouging and crashes.
; (4) Confirm cylinder diameter matches the value used to generate toolpaths.
; (5) Set A-axis datum — use the TNC Datum Setup screen to zero the A axis
;     at your reference position.
; (6) Air-cut with spindle off at 10% feed override before a real cut.
; (7) Confirm your TNC machine parameters for the A-axis are correct:
;     axis limits, acceleration, max RPM. Check MP7420 (axis assignment)
;     and MP1000 (rotary axis configuration).
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Retract order: lift Z to safe clearance before commanding large A moves.
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; See docs/MACHINES.MD — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): {{machine.workAreaMm.x}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.y}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.z}}
{{#if machine.aAxisRangeDeg}}; A-axis range: {{machine.aAxisRangeDeg}} deg — verify against TNC MP axis limits
{{/if}}
; --- Safety header ---
{{units}}              ; millimeters — must match TNC setting
G90                    ; absolute distance mode (X Y Z A all absolute)
G17                    ; XY plane for G2/G3 arcs
G40                    ; cancel cutter radius compensation
G49                    ; cancel tool length compensation
G80                    ; cancel canned cycles
{{#if wcsLine}}; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54-G59 selection
{{wcsLine}}
{{/if}}
{{#if operationLabel}}; Operation: {{operationLabel}}
{{/if}}
; --- Tool call (Heidenhain DIN/ISO mode — verify tool in TNC tool table) ---
T{{#if toolNumber}}{{toolNumber}}{{else}}1{{/if}} M6                  ; select tool {{#if toolNumber}}{{toolNumber}}{{else}}1{{/if}} and execute tool change
G43 H{{#if toolNumber}}{{toolNumber}}{{else}}1{{/if}}                 ; apply tool length compensation from TNC tool table
; Home / safe position — retract Z before rotating A to avoid collisions
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}}   ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
; Spindle on (Heidenhain — confirm S value and M3/M4 match your spindle config)
{{spindleOn}}
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}; --- Inverse-time feed mode (G93) for continuous rotary axis motion ---
; F-word = 1/time (inverse minutes). Each G1 block must carry its own F value.
; G94 is restored after the toolpath to return to normal feed-per-minute mode.
G93                    ; inverse-time feed mode ON
{{/if}}; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
{{#each toolpathLines}}
{{this}}
{{/each}}
; --- end toolpath ---
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}G94                    ; restore feed-per-minute mode
{{/if}}; Spindle off
{{spindleOff}}
; Safe retract and park
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}}   ; full retract for unload
G0 A0                  ; return A-axis to zero
G0 X0 Y0              ; park X Y — adjust to your preferred park position
M30                    ; program end
